      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"2. KERI JUNIOR below best last time at this track (30.66) in a Class 2/3, finishing a 5.5 lengths fourth. Looks the one to beat with even luck. 6. BARTLETT tends to drift back and work into the race, charging home into the minors two back before winding up late into second (26.25) in a Class 4 at Ascot Park last time. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Leading chance. 8. DEVIL DELIA is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 0.7 lengths at this track in a handy 30.27 beating Smelly Halle. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. 4. GLASSES can fill a top-three spot. Faces a significant drop in class today.\",\"runners\":[2,6,8,4],\"exclusive\":false}",
